# Prevent syncthing from corrupting git/jj internals.
#
# Ignore the ENTIRE .git and .jj directories. Syncing only parts of .git
# (e.g. refs/HEAD without objects, or objects without refs) leaves each
# machine with a half-built object store — refs point at objects that were
# never synced over, which is exactly what produced the "tree not found"
# corruption that broke jj here. Each machine keeps its own local .git/.jj
# and syncs commits the normal way (git push/pull).
.git
.jj
.jj.broken-*
*.sync-conflict-*